P0.3 Fix: Nil Store Guards

## Problem
11 unguarded p.store.* accesses in aws.go could cause nil pointer panic
if store initialization fails. Lines 967-968 also silently ignored errors.

## Solution
1. Added checkStore() helper method that:
   - Checks if p.store is nil
   - Returns ErrInvalidState with descriptive message
   - Prevents panic with graceful error handling

2. Added guard at entry of 7 methods:
   - planInfra (line 611)
   - approvePlan (line 867)
   - createInfra (line 920)
   - deploy (line 1211)
   - status (line 1446)
   - teardown (line 1513)
   - deploymentsResource (line 3123)

3. Fixed silent error suppression:
   - Lines 989-996: Changed from _, _ to proper error logging
   - Now logs with slog.Warn for visibility

## Testing
Added TestNilStoreGuard with 7 subtests confirming all methods
return proper error instead of panicking when store is nil.

